						<div class="postbody">Oh I see, well of course I would be the last person trying to wave a flag and bitch about why something is not being developed further instantly, I've got a lot of time to do it as well from what I can tell so I don't depend on anything here, if necessary I'll go with the text version. If needed eventually, I'd be happy to find useful similarities between Pently and Famitracker, but like dougeff said, it might be unnecessary.<br /><br />For example, demanding the use of certain instrument names in Famitracker, so that upon conversion, certain Famitracker instruments can be interpreted as instruments or attack settings.</div>

