						<div class="postbody">When I made a spreadsheet to double-check the pitch table from the wiki (it has a few rounding errors) I think I had some kind of column with how many bits a sweep needed to be, but I forget what condition I put on it.<br /><br />I came to the obvious-in-retrospect observation that you get one extra bit of period (be it in its simple play-this-note or the amount you need to sweep to get to the next note in N steps) each octave.</div>

